\begin_layout Section
Update Law
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moreover, we are comparing whether or not putting the adaptive feedforward
 term (a ResNet) performs better in the integral or not in the integral.
 Use the same update laws for both.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\dot{\widehat{\theta}}=\text{proj}\left(\Gamma\left(\left(\left|\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial\theta}\right|_{\left(x,\widehat{\theta}\right)}\right)^{\top}\left(e\right)-k_{\widehat{\theta}}\widehat{\theta}\right)\right)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $k_{\widehat{\theta}}>0$
\end_inset

 is user-selected.
 Projection's code was given.
 If you need to see the paper it came from, say so now.
 It is NOT Kristic's projection operator.
 Here, notice that I use the convention that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial\theta}\right|_{\left(x,\widehat{\theta}\right)}\in\mathbb{R}^{n\times p}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\widehat{\theta}\in\mathbb{R}^{p}$
\end_inset

.
 Let
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\dot{\Gamma} & =\alpha I_{p}+\beta\Gamma-\gamma\Gamma^{2}-\Gamma\frac{\left(\left|\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial\theta}\right|_{\left(x,\widehat{\theta}\right)}\right)^{\top}\left(\left|\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial\theta}\right|_{\left(x,\widehat{\theta}\right)}\right)}{1+\nu\left\Vert \left|\frac{\partial\Phi}{\partial\theta}\right|_{\left(x,\widehat{\theta}\right)}\right\Vert ^{2}}\Gamma\\
\alpha & =\frac{\overline{\Gamma}\underline{\Gamma}^{3}}{\overline{\Gamma}^{2}-\underline{\Gamma}^{2}}\\
\beta & =\underline{\Gamma}\\
\gamma & =\frac{\underline{\Gamma}\overline{\Gamma}}{\overline{\Gamma}^{2}-\underline{\Gamma}^{2}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{\Gamma}>\underline{\Gamma}>0$
\end_inset

 are user-specified.
 Symmetric is critical for 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

, so normalize at every step, i.e., with 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma=\frac{1}{2}\Gamma^{\top}+\frac{1}{2}\Gamma$
\end_inset

 or a similar method.
 
\end_layout

